What you don’t know can cause you serious grief and Big name companies have duped the public into thinking auto insurance is some sort of “off the shelf” product where “one size fits all”. That fallacy can cause your financial ruin! Basic Coverages Normally Included Liability Liability coverage on your auto insurance is the most critical portion of your It is the coverage that pays out if you hurt someone in an accident, or if you cause any damage to property that doesn’t belong to When you consider the cost of medical bills, or the cost of cars on the road today, it’s no wonder why your liability insurance is the one portion of your auto insurance that you do not want to skimp Amazingly enough, your liability coverage is often times the cheapest part of your The cost to double, triple, or quadruple your auto liability coverage is For the same cost as a few Starbucks coffees for you and your friends, you could add ten times the amount of liability coverage to your When shopping for your auto insurance, be wary of any proposal or quote that offers the state minimum coverage for Tennessee minimum limits are 50K 15K What this means, is if you are involved in an accident that is your fault, and the other vehicle has three passengers who all have various levels of injuries, your auto insurance will only pay out $25,000 per person, as a maximum, however the policy will not pay any more than $50,000 for the entire The number in this liability limit represents the amount of coverage $15,000 for property damage that you are responsible for With the average cost of a new car above $36,000 , it’s is our professional recommendation to carry higher limits of property Any payout or settlement beyond those numbers will need to come from you These decisions are often made in a court setting when the other party has decided to sue With the high amount of fraud that takes place, it is a scary proposition to gamble with lower limits of Because of the low costs, and our belief that you deserve more, at The Client’s Insurance Agency, we will never offer an auto insurance proposal with inadequate, or state minimums for liability and property damage – Get a quote for better liability insurance here . Medical Payments This coverage pays for medical injuries sustained by passengers in your vehicle during an Many agents quote a standard $5,000 in medical payments on every We have options to increase this coverage to as high as $100,000 if Uninsured Motorist What if we told you that % of the drivers you drive next to each and every day is uninsured? Sound frightening? Sound impossible? California Consumer Privacy Act Recent news about data breaches and perceived of personal data handling has caused growing global consumer distrust in how their personal information is being In response, in the European Union enacted the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) a sweeping landmark law protecting consumers data privacy California followed suit by passing the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA) marking it the first state to meaningfully address these growing consumer A broad summary of key provisions are highlighted Penalties The stakes are high with fines up to $7,500 per consumer failure and estimated total state privacy expenditures of $5B by Who is Impacted? Generally, any businesses conducting business in California or who collects or processes personal consumer data of California residents AND who also meets one of the following criteria is impacted: Revenue $25MM+ OR Data of ,000 Californian consumers, OR Derives %+ of revenue selling (renting, disclosing, transferring ) consumer data What New Rights Do Consumers Have? The intent of the CCPA is to provide consumers with greater control over how their personal data is Consumers will have the right to: Request what personal data that is being collected about them and with whom it is being To of the “sale” of their Request that their data be deleted by the Right to equal service and What Must You Do? This conditional funding commitment signifies the latest development milestone for the The Advanced Clean Energy Storage hydrogen hub, located in Delta, Utah, was announced in May , and within three years is in the final stages of debt and equity Currently, the hub has secured all major contracts including offtake engineer, procure and construct (EPC) contractors major equipment suppliers, and Operations and Maintenance (O&M) Haddington Ventures, the financial advisor for the hub and equity sponsor of Magnum Development, is securing $650MM through its Equity Syndication These critical financial investments will ensure the future growth and scalability of the “We are unbelievably excited to reach this important milestone, not just for our hub, but for the hydrogen industry as a whole,” said Michael Ducker, Senior Vice President of Hydrogen Infrastructure for Mitsubishi Power Americas and President of Advanced Clean Energy Storage “Equally rewarding is having spent the past year partnering and working with such a and incredibly talented team from the Intermountain Power Agency to trail blaze this market leading We are honored to be sharing this industry moment with them Casual, Comfortable Clothes: Our atmosphere is casual and While attire is provided during care stays, usually lasting days, comfortable clothing to wear to the next level of care is Personal Hygiene Items: Pack your toothpaste, toothbrush, deodorant, and shampoo, Prescription Medications: Pack your medications (in the original bottle with doctor prescribed protocol) in a plastic Ziplock bag to bring with These will be locked in an office and return to you, after your care Cell phones: There are some restrictions as to when and where you can use your cell phone, but you may bring it with If your phone has a camera, be respectful of the anonymity of our Please, only take pictures with other individuals if you have their permission and do not post pictures on social There is a blackout period where you will not be able to use your cell CrossRoads provides all meals and Outside food is not allowed during your of As you transition to higher levels of care, you may have access to outside food What Can I leave at Home? Bayes: a creative tool for thinking and speaking with data BAYES mark Why isn t data more human ? It’s and data isn’t just in the analyst department It’s everywhere you look — in the news you read, the apps you use, and the services that power your business: product metrics, marketing surveys, transactions, HR The list goes But how often do you really look at this stuff? Sure, everyone talks about being “data-driven,” but in reality, no one really Why? Data is alien, spreadsheets aren’t Long rows and columns of black and white text on a screen just don’t mean much to Most existing tools expect you to be a data scientist — versed in jargon, programming, and manual The rest treat you like you’re a suit in a stock photo — reading over Business Intelligence™ white papers and refreshing KPIs on quarterly In either case, you’re wading through endless menus, dials, and tweaking , just to get a single chart on the It’s death by about a thousand paper cuts as you spend more time thinking about driving the software than you do on what the data is trying to tell We believe there is a better way We’re excited to bring you BAYES — a creative, tool for thinking and speaking with Bayes helps you use your data as evidence for sharpening your decision making, making clearer arguments, and improving your business — no matter who you Join our waitlist to stay tuned: Join The team behind Bayes Will Strimling Product at Research at Interactive Data Data viz at FiveThirtyEight, Harvard Kennedy CS at University of Justin Woodbridge Product at Engineering at Integral Built Raffle Data viz Harvard Kennedy CS at Columbia Trevor Shibley Engineer Engineering at Dropbox, Amazon, Bloomberg, CS at University of Will Wilkinson Designer Creator of Manual, Everyday, and Design at Director at Our investors Amplify Partners Y Combinator © Bayes Technologies Twitter LinkedIn AngelList Contact We re Hiring!
